# React Query, Cache, and Testing Safety

## 1) Query Key Discipline

- query keys must be centralized per feature
- avoid inline ad-hoc keys spread across files
- when touching notes, prefer moving toward the same dedicated key-module pattern already used by learning and study questions
- use stable query key factories with intent-revealing names

## 2) Mutation Synchronization

- prefer invalidation after mutation where possible
- manual cache patching is allowed only when truly necessary and must be justified
- optimistic updates are not the default in this project
- any mutation must explicitly identify which queries become stale

## 3) Cache Safety

- do not let stale cache create fake learning eligibility or hide recent grading
- avoid duplicating the same data across multiple caches without a reason
- when a mutation changes note lifecycle, review status, study questions, or sessions, verify all affected surfaces refresh correctly

## 4) Required Test Targets

Add or update tests for important logic changes, especially:
- review eligibility and same-day gating
- timezone-sensitive date logic
- session construction and snapshot behavior
- scheduling calculations
- mapping and normalization helpers
- trash/restore/hard-delete domain transitions
- reducers, selectors, and pure state transitions
- bug fixes in previously unstable logic

## 5) Testing Strategy

This project currently has limited API tests and no active Playwright usage.
Therefore:
- prioritize strong automated tests around critical logic and domain-sensitive behavior
- prefer unit and integration-style tests around pure logic and orchestration boundaries
- if UI behavior is critical, structure code so it can be tested without relying on end-to-end tooling

## 6) When No Test Is Added

If no test is added for a risky change, explicitly state:
- why a test was not added
- what manual verification was used instead
- what residual risk remains

## 7) Verification Expectations After Changes

Report:
- invalidated queries
- tests added/updated
- manual flows checked
- any known stale-data risks or follow-up refactors needed, such as incomplete query-key centralization
